<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">
Yeah but aren't our raptures lure based now after the last patch that improved several of our spells?<P>If thats the case, seems to me no other stat is really needed.<P>I could see using rapture on a myconoid adept that has just popped and is casting CH.  You really don't have time to figure out if its level 56 or not, you just need it to stop CHing the myconoid warrior and you need it to stop NOW!<P>I really can't see how HP or CHA would make a difference in either case, cept I can see how HP would make a difference against monsters that hit in the 100-220 range (frogs, lizards, spiders, myconoids, shissars, juggers etc... etc..).  An extra 700hp could keep you alive long enough to get off another mez or root or rapture or have a tank taunt off of you.<P>When you get agro on something that hits for 300-700 and hits for 2-4 times a round, 700 HP doesn't last that much longer, unless its slowed but our tashes usually come before something is slowed.  heheh<P>I could see HP making a difference in encounters like ToV that have the AE breathe.  If you can last through an entire fight on your HP without getting below the HP level that gives you unconditional agro,  that would allow clerics to spend their mana on tanks instead of you.  Then you just get a donals BP heal during downtime between wurms.<P>ToV kinda pisses me off, at level 60, with resist gear, druid buffs and bard song I might have 300 almost 400 fire/cold resist.  And those AEs *STILL* get through from time to time for full damage.  But with the resists I get quite a few partial damage AEs for 60-120 damage.<P>Oh wait, I'm supposed to be beating the dead horse some more...  BAD HORSE!  THWAP!<P>- Pahbi
</font>
