<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">
Exactly, when using Rapture no other stat is needed.  So if you absolutely 100% need a mob locked down immediately, Rapture it    <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  With this kind of mindset 95% of the situations where you have people claiming they need Charisma or need HP/AC to survive get tossed out the window    <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>I suppose there are two reasons to using Rapture, one is to mezz the highest level mobs possible, the ones GoK bounces on ... of course I think I have encountered two that GoK bounced on unexpectedly in my career as an enchanter and it surprised the hell outta me both times.  The second to to guarentee a lockdown, I have never seen Rapture resisted on a mob unless it was in some odd way immune to Rapture (Rock Golems in the hole).<P>I use rapture when I know if I do not manage to mezz the mob then it is likely I or someone else is going to die.<P>Sure, I could use GoK on that Pool of Slime in CT (Level 57), but it might bounce and if it does, I am going to get my arse handed to me.  So I Rapture it, Tash it, Slow it and them when Rapture pops  I GoK it.  It is hitting my like a weak kitten for a mere 200-300hp per round instead of 800-1000hp    <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>Those lifestealer mosquito's?  Yep they can range in level from 53 to 57 meaning some are Dazzleable and some are GoKable.  Have one of those as an add, no problem ... Rapture, debuff, rapture pops, try dazzle, it bounces try GoK    <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>You only get issues when the puller brings back several higher level mobs, then suddenly you have to rely on GoK and cross your fingers  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  <P>Worst I have seen in CT:<P>2x Pool of Slime (100% GoKable)<BR>1x Crystalline Mass (100% GoKable)<BR>2x Swirling Slime (100% Dazzlable)<BR>1x LifeStealer Mosquito (Dazzle/GoK depending)<BR>1x Ooze (100% Dazzlable)<P>The puller called 2 Pools and when he arrived in camp with the backspawn I had the first 5 mobs listed to deal with.  Then in the course of the battle, the room spawned and I was up to 7 mobs to deal with.  This is when having a high HP/AC saved my arse  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>I max out my hp to allow the cleric greater options on keeping the party alive.  I also have clerics that complete heal me.  It was much more impressive when I only had 2300hp full buffed and they would complete heal me.  Now that I have 3500hp fully buffed it is not quite as impressive but still very cool and very mana efficient   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>Regards,<br /><br />--------------------<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65288" target="_blank">Sage Zanithar TideBreaker</a><br />Phantasmist <br />The Relentless, Cazic Thule<br />
</font>
