<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">
I don't think any test will ever prove or disprove the usefulness of CHA.  There are just too many variables to consider besides changing your CHA around.<P>What level are you?<BR>What level is the mob?<BR>How magic resistant is the mob?<BR>Which mezz spell are you using?<P>I could go to Sebilis with my level 60 Enchanter with 95CHA and get a mezz off everytime on a frog.  A level 50 Enchanter, could go to the same zone with 200CHA and have his mezz resisted 30% of the time.<P>On the same token, I could go to PoH with 200CHA and try to mezz revs (which are fairly resistant) and have 50% of my mezzes resisted and another Enchanter with 100CHA could go to Karnor's and have 5% of their's resisted.<P>I think the most logical arguement I have heard is that CHA does help against mezzing mobs, but not as much as level does.  So, a level 53 Enchanter will have less trouble mezzing a level 50 mob than a level 50 Enchanter, but the level 50 Enchanter won't have as much trouble if he ups his CHA some.  Of course, that is hard to prove too.<P>Me?  I play it safe.  It's not that hard to get your CHA near 200 at 60, especially not with a 50cha buff.  I currently sit at 1911hp, 736ish ac, 221int and 199cha.  I have 199cha, and I honestly don't wear any items for the CHA:<P>Earrings:  Jade Inlaid Hoop / Earring of Blazing Energy - I wear them for the good HP and Mana.<P>Necklace - Derasinel's Talisman - Worn for the goo HP/AC/INT/Mana<P>Bracer - Bracelet of Bueaty - Worn for the AC and resists.<P>Shoulders - Runed Coldain Prayer Shawl - Worn primarily for the FT1 effect, but I put so much work into getting one that I'm not looking to upgrade anytime soon (unless I get another FT item).<P>Robe - Robe of Benevolence - Worn for the AC/INT/HP/Mana - Something I am looking to upgrade though.<P>Back - Cloak of Heirophant - One of the best Caster cloaks out there.<P>That's 52CHA right there.  Add the 50 CHA buff and that's 102CHA.  I'm sure most Enchanters have over 100 base CHA.<P>My point - You don't have to neglect other skills in order to get CHA up.  It's not hard to get CHA up since it is usually added to items for Enchanters in such large quantities anyways.<br /><br />--------------------<br /><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=43477" target="_blank">Cantatus</a> of The Haven<br />Karana Server<br /><i>"Ego sum callidior quam tu quod possum legere hoc."</i><br />
</font>
