What Hikaru and Llorian are trying to say is that they, like myself and most others tend to pickup Charisma gear on the side while we are pursing our normal equipment goals.  It is not completely off the list as equipment goals, it just sits behind:<P>AC/HP/Mana/Int/Mana Regen<P>in order of importance.<P>I mean seriously, outside of high end gear like NToV we will be wearing our Velious armor for the most part.  Great AC, great HP, great int, great mana and some charisma to boot.  A few pieces will be replaced with other armor.  Heck our Epic has a nice chunk of charisma on it.  But I do not wield it for the charisma.<P>My Buffed charisma is 202, I do not wear a single piece of equipment for charisma purposes.  A large amount of the enchanter armor just has charisma on it.  VI tends to put charisma on our class based armor & weapons as well as a good number of pure caster items.<P>So although my priorities are to get my AC between 700 - 800 and then full on hp after that, in doing so I have several pieces of gear that have charisma and thus jack my charisma up over 200.<P>Funny thing is I am even wearing a piece of negative charisma equipment  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  Fingerbone hoop is quite a useful item.<P>So not one single piece of equipment I am wearing is specifically for the charisma, but it is not like I am deliberately trying to remove all charisma gear from my equipment list either.  I know it has a small effect, I am just not catering to it because I do not find it to be worth the extra effort.<P>As for a glorious point, I have been through dozens and dozens of Charisma posts with Llorian and Hikaru, so I already know how they feel on the subject.<P>Hikaru:<BR>Actually I believe most of the tests showed that a substantial shift in charisma will yield about a 10% chance of of failed mezz succeeding.  Which works out to between a 2 to 5% increase on each actual mezz attempt succeeding.<P>I remember arguing on one that the check between a 70 charisma and a 230 charisma was a little extreme given that some other stats are shown to have a breakpoint at 70.  That particular test showed a greater skew in the success/failure rate with high vs low charisma.<P>Tunzell:<BR>Once again, I am not laughing at you because you are in the charisma camp.  I have also never stated you are an idiot for being in the charisma camp.  For that matter I have never stated you were an idiot at all.  <P>Seems a little crude to come right out and state it, I would much rather just point out all the insults and inconsistancies in your argument and let others come up with their own conculsions about that     <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>I cannot help but wonder since you keep stating that you are upset at me calling you an idiot, and I have never done this, that perhaps you have an inferiority complex.  There are people that can help you with that.<P>Regards,<br /><br />--------------------<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65288" target="_blank">Sage Zanithar TideBreaker</a><br />Phantasmist <br />The Relentless, Cazic Thule<br />
