<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">
While your math is correct, Hikaru, you've been misled due to the fact that most of the people on the forum don't differentiate between percents and percentage points.<P>The generally accepted figure is that going from low cha to high cha affects resist rates by at least 5 percentage points, not 5%. (Depends, of course, on what cha is considered low, and what is high) Meaning that it might change a 15% resist rate to a 10% resist rate, or a 40% resist rate to a 35% resist rate.<P>Unfortunately, people insist on calling that a 5% difference.<P>Redoing your calculations for, say, example 3: The person with low cha has a 15% resist rate, leading to 90 resists in a 10 hour timespan. Person B with high cha would, however, have a 10% resist rate, having 60 resists in a 10 hour timespan. The difference here is 30 more mobs, not 5, or alternatively a 33% reduction in resists.<P>Arlina
</font>
