ing that I, just as you could sit down, blow 8 hours and do the tests. The question is, why should I? You want the answers ... you go do the test. I am already happy, at 60 charisma is meaningless, anything I NEED mezzed gets Raptured, outside of that I use Dazzle/GoK and if it gets resisted I could care less, if I cared I would have used Rapture. <BR>No Insight there just common sense</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE>/shrug, dude just can&#8217;t help his self.  He&#8217;s got to get his opinion in, just can&#8217;t seem to figure out how to back it up.    <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Same post:<BR><B>On a good number of post you undoubtably read looking for Charisma articles, you probably saw me supplying the same links you did above and more. I have read them all, a few I even contributed to</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE>This is a technical impossibility me thinks.    <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Same post:<BR><B>I take no offense whatsoever to people that choose to max their Charisma, I believe it is a waste of time but who am I to tell you how to play your character. I know clerics that max their AC too, welcome to the world, not everyone uses the wheel ... lots of people reinvent it and in doing so understand it better. Question the status quo, it is always a good idea.</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE>Just as I later stated, this is just a statement made to belittle those that would disagree with Zan&#8230;    <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Same post:<BR><B>What I do take offense to is people posting that Charisma "obviously" has an effect on mezzing because whenever they get a string of resists they look up and find their charisma buff is down. <BR>I take offense to people posting that Charisma does or does not affect things and providing no proof beyond their "feelings". <BR>And I take offense to people that "Throw down the gauntlet" oh, about once a week or so and demand the Enchanter