<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">
Sounds to me like none of it is really gonna matter much in any situation.<P>CHA probably doesn't make enough difference to noticeable, if it does make a difference, its likely to be against things where your right on the edge of getting the spell to land, and just need a bit of a boost. (best analogy I've heard)  CHA could probably be renamed as, 'luck' and be more applicable to what its actually doing for you.<P>AC probably doesn't make enough difference to be noticeable, 800ac might make smigeon amount of difference if you parse it long enough, but the chanter with 600-700ac isn't going to be far behind, it might even be so close that you statistically can't tell the difference.<P>HP *CAN* make a difference if you get ALOT of them (an extra 600-1000), to buy you a *TINY* amount extra time to get an extra mez, root, mem-blur, rapture or what have you off.  My own personal experience tho is that the chanter with ~2700hp can perform just as well, as the chanter with ~3200hp.<P>HP probably *WON'T* make a difference against something that hits for 300-700 and gets double or quad attacks.  Lets face it, your going down like a wet paper bag, and nothing in the world is gonna stop it.  Not to mention the fact that everyone is gonna pissed if you suck up a bunch of mana that could have been better spent on a tank.<P>Another point to consider, by level 60, your not likely to be wearing any single item that just gives HP, or mana, or cha or what not.  Everything you own will have multiple stats, +hp, +mana, +int, +cha +resists etc.<P>That almost makes the equipment selection a no brainer.  You look at the item that just dropped, look at the item your wearing, if it has more stats and is an upgrade, you roll, and pray you win.<P>For casters, stats just don't seem to have that much of an impact, int give you more mana.  Everything else is pretty much cake, extra HP, extra mana, extra this or extra that is nice to have, but not having it isn't going to keep you from being a great enchanter.  Thats just the way the game is designed.<P>- Pahbi
</font>
