<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">
My drive for HP comes from a different direction.  Do not get me wrong, I feel extra hp = extra time for the heal to land but it is more than that for me.<P>I have a mana robe and I use it alot, HP = Mana for me.  More importantly, HP = Mana without Aggro.<P>I can stand and Robe thereby avoiding the sit aggro.<P>HP also allows the cleric a more efficient method of healing me.  The more HP I have, the longer I live, the longer I live, the better chance that the cleric can land a CH on me   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>More than this, if I have more HP, the cleric will not be crouching out of a CH on the MA because he knows I can last long enough to let it go thru and still keep me alive.<P>For charming, the additional HP = additional time to get my Charmie under control.<P>Having a lot of hp means I have additional choices.  Do I "Have" to hold these mobs stun locked or can I afford a round of hits to lock one down.  <P>But I suppose the best reason I like HP is because my friends like to challenge me by trying to kill me   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  HP often let me survive those 16 mob pulls   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>I suppose in the end, I feel that HP grant me both efficiency and extends my available choices in a given situation.  It definately does with the mana robe and when I am in zones where I can use a ManaStone the effects of additional HP are rather staggering.<P>Fully buffed I only have 3514 HP ATM  <IMG SRC="frown.gif" border="0"><P>Regards,<br /><br />--------------------<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65288" target="_blank">Sage Zanithar TideBreaker</a><br />Phantasmist <br />The Relentless, Cazic Thule<br />
</font>
